'''Kumar Paudel''' ({{lang-ne|'''कुमार पौडेल'''}}) is a Nepalese conservationist focused on most threatened wildlife; co-founder and director of Greenhood Nepal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.myrepublica.com/news/14956 |title= On the brink |work= Republica |accessdate= 9 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.rufford.org/projects/kumar_paudel |title= Kumar Paudel |work= rufford.org |accessdate= 9 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2015-11-02/an-environmentalists-guide-to-books.html |title= An environmentalist’s guide to books |work= The Kathmandu Post |accessdate= 9 March 2017}}</ref> He has designed and conducting ground breaking conservation research and programs in Nepal. He is extensively into curb illegal wildlife trade and scale up pangolin conservation initiatives in Nepal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2013-02-26/conservation-school-for-awareness.html|title=Conservation school for awareness|access-date=2017-10-21|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nepalitimes.com/article/Nepali-Times-Buzz/protecting-the-pangolin,3597|title=Protecting less known species {{!}} Nepali Times Buzz {{!}} Nepali Times|last=Shrestha|first=Shreejana|website=nepalitimes.com|access-date=2017-10-21}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2015-02-21/illegal-trade-of-pangolin-grew-eight-fold.html|title=Illegal trade of pangolin grew ‘eight-fold’|access-date=2017-10-21|language=en}}</ref> He has been awarded a fellowship at [[University of Oxford]], within the Oxford Martin Programme on the Illegal Wildlife Trade.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iccs.org.uk/person/kumar-paudel|title=Kumar Paudel {{!}} Interdisciplinary Centre for Conservation Science|website=www.iccs.org.uk|language=en|access-date=2017-10-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://jacobphelps.wixsite.com/enviro-policy-lab/single-post/2017/07/18/Kumar-wins-prestigious-Oxford-Fellowship|title=enviro-policy-lab|work=enviro-policy-lab|access-date=2017-10-20}}</ref> He is also a producer of the critically acclaimed documentary ''Looking The Un-eyed Way'' with Pradeep Bashyal and [[Ankit Babu Adhikari]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2012-09-17/a-story-of-resilience.html|title=A story of resilience|work= The Kathmandu Post|accessdate= 8 March 2017}}</ref>

