[[Tony Stewart]] is an American racing driver who won three [[NASCAR]] [[Sprint Cup Series]] championships. Over the course of his racing career, Stewart won multiple NASCAR races, 49 of which were in NASCAR's Sprint Cup Series.
==NASCAR==
===Sprint Cup Series=== In the Cup Series, Tony Stewart, the [[NASCAR Rookie of the Year|1999 Rookie of the Year]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Caraviello|first=David|url=http://www.nascar.com/en_us/news-media/articles/2014/1/20/top-10-nascar-rookies-tony-stewart-jimmie-johnson-dale-earnhardt.html|title=Top 10 Rookie Campaigns at NASCAR's Highest Level|work=[[NASCAR]]|publisher=NASCAR Digital Media, LLC|date=January 20, 2014|accessdate=June 29, 2017}}</ref> and three-time series champion, has won 49 races at 21 different tracks.
