{{Multiple issues| {{COI|date=September 2016}} {{BLP primary sources|date=November 2015}} }} {{Infobox person | name = Olly Smith | birth_name = Olly Smith | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1974|9|18}} | birth_place = [[Jersey]] | nationality = British | occupation = British TV presenter, wine expert, columnist and author. | years_active = | notable_works = }}
'''Olly Smith''' (born 18 September 1974) is a British TV presenter, wine expert, columnist and author.
==Family background== His brother is the comedian and writer [[Will Smith (comedian)|Will Smith]],.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://twitter.com/jollyolly/status/63616733273014272 |title=Olly Smith on Twitter: "@tvpeanuts Yes I am related to Will Smith! I'm delighted to reveal that he is my brother, do follow him @willsmithuk" |publisher=Twitter.com |date=2011-04-28 |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> Olly Smith was born in [[Jersey]].<ref>https://www.sundaypost.com/news/world-news/my-favourite-holiday-olly-smith/</ref> He lives in [[Sussex]] with his family.<ref name="ollysmith1">{{cite web|url=http://www.ollysmith.com/about/ |title=About |publisher=Olly Smith |date=2014-11-11 |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref>
==Writing== Smith is wine editor of ''The Mail on Sunday'''s Event Magazine and writes a weekly wine column.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}} He has formerly written columns for ''[[Wine & Spirit]]'', ''[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]'', and [[Waitrose]] and [[Sainsbury's]] supermarket magazines, and features for such publications as ''[[The Independent on Sunday]]'', ''[[London Lite]]'', and ''[[Country Life (magazine)|Country Life]]''.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}
Smith has written three books, ''Eat & Drink: Good Food That’s Great to Drink With''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ollysmith.com/shop/books/eat-drink-signed-copy/ |title=Eat & Drink, signed copy |publisher=Olly Smith |date=2014-11-11 |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> in 2010, ''Wine: Both Barrels''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ollysmith.com/shop/categories/wine-both-barrels-signed-copy/ |title=Wine: Both Barrels, signed copy |publisher=Olly Smith |date=2014-11-11 |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> in 2012, and ''Behind Enemy Wines''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ollysmith.com/shop/books/behind-enemy-wines-signed-copy/ |title=Behind Enemy Wines, signed copy |publisher=Olly Smith |date= |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> in 2013.
Smith previously wrote for film and TV including [[Pingu]], [[Wallace and Gromit]] and [[Charlie and Lola]].<ref name="ollysmith1"/>
==Television == Smith regularly appears as a wine expert on BBC1's ''[[Saturday Kitchen]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ollysmith.com/media/television/saturday-kitchen/ |title=BBC Saturday Kitchen |publisher=Olly Smith |date= |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> and is a frequent guest on ITV's ''[[This Morning (TV programme)|This Morning]]''. In September 2014 Smith presented a four-part series ''Last Taste of Summer'', which aired on ''This Morning''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ollysmith.com/media/television/last-taste-summer/ |title=Last Taste of Summer |publisher=Olly Smith |date=2014-11-11 |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref>
Smith was host of the short-lived ''[[Iron Chef UK]]'' during 2010.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}
In 2011, Smith presented a ten-part series for Channel 4 entitled ''The Secret [[supper club|Supper Club]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/the-secret-supper-club |title=The Secret Supper Club - All 4 |publisher=Channel4.com |date=2015-02-12 |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> Outside of the UK, he presented a documentary series about [[Chilean wine]], ''Uncorking the South'', for [[Canal 13 (Chile)|Canal 13]].{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}
He is also a [[voice artist|voice-over artist]], narrating ''Chic Eats'' for The [[Discovery Channel]], performing voices for [[ITV Network|ITV]] show ''[[The Amazing Adrenalini Brothers]]'' as well as writing and presenting ''Dude, Where's My Title?'' for [[BBC Radio 4]]. He also performed alongside [[Roger Moore]] in ''The Fly Who Loved Me'' Christmas cartoon for [[United Nations Children's Fund|UNICEF]].
==Awards== In 2011, Smith was named by Off License News among the top 75 most influential people in the UK wine trade.<ref>Off Licence News, 16 May 2011, Top 75 Most Influential People in Wine</ref>
*United Kingdom Vineyards Association Communicator of the Year 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ollysmith.com/olly-wins-communicator-of-the-year-5848/ |title=Olly wins Communicator of the Year! |publisher=Olly Smith |date= |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> *Roederer Awards Finalist for International Columnist of the Year 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theroedererawards.com/shortlist2012.html |title=Louis Roederer Wine Writers Awards &#124; finalists |publisher=Theroedererawards.com |date= |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> *Wines of Portugal Journalism Award 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ollysmith.com/olly-wins-journalism-award-4912/ |title=Olly wins Journalism Award! |publisher=Olly Smith |date= |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> *International Wine & Spirits Communicator of the Year Award 2009 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tizwine.com/index.php/ps_pagename/pdfpressrelease/news/1420/.pdf |format=PDF |title=IWSC Communicator of the Year 2009 announced at Vinitaly Gala opening night |date=April 2009 |publisher=Tizwine.com |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref> *Drinks Business Young Achiever of the Year Award 2009 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedrinksbusiness.com/awards/drinks-business-awards-2009/ |title=Drinks Business Awards 2009 |publisher=Thedrinksbusiness.com |date=1970-01-01 |accessdate=2015-11-25}}</ref>
