'''Oumar Balde''' (1931&ndash;?) was a [[Guinea]]n engineer. He served a director of the Highways Department and secretary-general of the [[Organization of States Bordering the Senegal River]] under [[Sékou Touré]]. After his arrest, he was neither tried nor sentenced,<ref>{{cite web|title=List of 78 "Disappeared" Prisoners|url=http://www.campboiro.org/bibliotheque/aiorg/hrv-prrg/list78.html|work=www.CampBoiro.org|accessdate=8 May 2013}}</ref> and is believed to have died in detention in [[Kindia]] {{when|date=March 2016}}.<ref name="Dictionary 2005">{{Cite book|author1=O'Toole, Thomas |author2=Baker, Janice E. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kIiHwg3Y5u4C&pg=PA3
|title=Historical Dictionary of Guinea|publisher=Volume 94 of African historical dictionaries, [[Scarecrow Press]]|year=2005|page=17|isbn=0-8108-4634-9}}</ref>

